text: I loved the original "National lampoons vacation" from the 80's, certainly a true classic. I do like how at least it's Rusty taking his family to wally world instead of another shit remake of a once classic film, I'll give this a chance before I say anything but I am already skeptical. I swear, it's been like 100 years now that we've been making movies and I'm saddened that so many piece of shit producers already have completely run out of anything new and original to make so they get lazy, take a childhood favorite and end up pissing in the faces of fans everywhere by ruining it for a paycheck. If I see one more full blown remake of a 70's or 80's film that does nothing besides insult the original, I'm going to be sick! I'm no professional writer but do occasionally write a short story here and there and if I can think of something new to write, Hollywood can do so too and I garentee that a shitty new film is still 100X better than seeing the same old idea repackaged for the 21st century only now it's terrible. The bottom line is either stop remaking classic films into shit or just don't make anything at all because having no movie out is still so much better than seeing a classic film insulted. If we don't stop this shit, soon we'll be seeing the day where "The Godfather ", "Star Wars", "Back to The Future" and every other truly classic film is ruined by turning it into an awful remake one summer so sony or some other pathetic production company can make a few more million dollars from the idiots who actually watch these disasters in the theater or even worse, buy them on DVD!

text: If you liked the old Vacation movies, do not go thinking this one will be the same. Â The old Vacation movies were great, but this one was awful. It is very out of character for the Vacation movie series. Parts of it were funny, a few parts of it referred back to the old movies, but overall, it does not fit in with the old movies. It is not family friendly. Not. Even. Close. Â Totally shocked at some of the things I saw, and now I can't un-see them. Â I went in thinking I could fondly reminisce about the old movies and get more of the same, but I walked out of this very sad and almost disturbed at what I saw. Â  Contains multiple scenes, Â suggestions, and innuendos about adult activities, homosexual activities, pedophilia, etc. Â Some of the scenes should have been straight up illegal. Â They did not â€œupdateâ€ this movie franchise for a new generation. Â They took the movie franchise straight into the sewer, and going simply by some of the clips from this trailer, that can be taken literally in addition to figuratively. Â Looking around the theater while watching this movie, I saw whole families there. Â I canâ€™t help but think the parents of those families must have been shocked. Â Not family friendly at all. The potential for a new Vacation movie could have been great, but this turned out absolutely awful.
